<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,404,429]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Etymology.</emphasis>
An adjective derived from the Latin noun “ 
<emphasis box="[844,918,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">spatha</emphasis>
”, a broad, two-edged sword without a point, meaning “spatha-shaped” or like a spatha, referring to the shape of the surstylus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
